metadata.name: Voltage Vipers Automaton #112
metadata.description:
Multiple snakes feed with electricity, grow, and are definitely going to lose the game and transform into an electrical circuit cellular automaton.

Press 's' to save a gif.
Press 'p' to stop/start the pulse.
Press 'a' to stop/start the animation.
Click on a wire cell to generate an electron.

metadata.name: Annum #868
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: terminal.msg #8
metadata.description:
A fake desktop with fake termnials.
Open as many terminals as your system is able to.
Weird messages may from.

ODDS:
The words are randomly picked from a .txt file.
0 to 5 Open terminals on start.
Random colors or 1 from 25 curated palettes.
4 font options.
3 typing speed modes

HOW:
Double click on the TERMINAL icon or press T for a new Terminal.
Press F to loop System fonts.
Press C to change the terminal text color to white / back to original color.
Click & hold to drag the terminals.

metadata.name: Imperium #433
metadata.description:
Imperium is a study of shapes and colors, and how a very small set of shapes and colors, when given equally simple rules, can create a great variety of patterns that may bring meaning to the viewer.

Press the s key for a quick download at the current resolution, and press the space bar to display the export and information menu.

For more information, read the collection guide:
https://medium.com/@MrMallory/imperium-the-collection-guide-cd9ab7e05aa0

Author:

metadata.name: Intertwined #213
metadata.description:
Intertwined began as a study of how to overlap randomized shapes at many intersection points while retaining consistency and physical accuracy. I initially envisioned vines growing on buildings, but over time Intertwined moved in a more abstract embroidery-like direction while retaining influences from that foundational concept.

Controls:
Key S: Save the output as a jpeg at the current resolution (only available once the piece has finished loading).
Key Arrow Up: Scale the resolution up by a multiple of 1080 pixels. There is no maximum. The current highest recommended scale-factor is 4x.
Key Arrow Down: Scale the resolution down by a multiple of 1080 pixels. 1080p is the minimum.
Key A: Skip the construction animation to show the final result immediately (please note that for pieces with a larger grid skipping the animation may cause a long pause).

Browser Support: Confirmed to work in Chrome Version 97.0.4692.71

metadata.name: Noisy Pixel Management #367
metadata.description:
Noisy Pixel Management offers an open edition available for one week. Minting is complimentary as a gesture of gratitude to my collectors and supporters. As suggested by the project's name, it revolves around the concept of noise and pixels, yielding minimalistic pieces with subdued color palettes.

Press "s" to save as PNG
